From 0df5816d738caad6d631f543d794051b242d668b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Assam Boudjelthia <assam.boudjelthia@qt.io>
Date: Tue, 28 Apr 2026 16:39:42 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 23/26] Android: implement system locale in QtCore directly

The Android system locale backend lived in the QPA platform
plugin as QAndroidSystemLocale, a QSystemLocale subclass.
Service processes built on QCoreApplication never load the
QPA plugin, so they fell back to the base QSystemLocale built
from qlocale_unix.cpp, which only reads POSIX env vars.
Android does not export those, so services were stuck on the
C locale and translations did not work.

Move the implementation to src/corelib/text, following the
same shape as qlocale_unix.cpp: override query() and
fallbackLocale() directly. The lazy QSystemLocale fallback
in qlocale.cpp now picks up the Android implementation
regardless of whether a QGuiApplication exists, so services
and GUI apps share the same JNI-based path.

Fixes: QTBUG-140482
Change-Id: I86e95ce142419abcdb09b9f1ce1093cfa4be47a3
